ggplot challenge

jrm




Can you recreate the plots below?

I created them using the datasets included by default and ggplot only. I didn’t do any transformations of any kind or installed extra packages. I am also not providing the code ;)

For each plot I am just including the dataset and maybe some clues. Try to replicate them, use your imagination and remember, google (or duckduckgo if you value your privacy) is your best friend!.

library(tidyverse)

Flippin’ boxplots

Here I’m using the diamonds dataset. Note that the orientation of the boxplots is flipped along the x-axis. The names in the color guide are reversed to match their order in the plot.

Rugged plot

mpg dataset. I am manually setting the color scale to “skyblue”, “salmon”, and “purple” over a dark theme.

2dense 2plot

mpg dataset again. Check density2d to see how I created the orange lines around the plot. The points have some noise added so they won’t overlap. Notice that the plot only shows the bottom and left lines (ie, no grids or full frame).

oh beehive!

The relationship between carat and price in the diamonds binned into 15 groups. The gradient color scale uses “skyblue” as the low point and “yellow” as the high.

regress me maybe

Using the iris data set, look at the relationship between sepal length and petal length and look for a trend (ie, a linear modeling approach). Is there a difference between the 3 species? Notice that the points and colors are different for each species. The grid has been faceted by species. Note how the scales vary freely along the y axis.
